parameters.description: Log of COTS intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_cots ≈ 2.0, representing potential to double population annually under ideal conditions.
Log of COTS carrying capacity (individuals/m²). Corresponds to K_cots ≈ 2.0, representing maximum sustainable density during outbreaks.
Log of COTS predation rate on fast coral (% cover/COTS/year). Corresponds to alpha_fast ≈ 0.5, representing preference for fast-growing Acropora species.
Log of COTS predation rate on slow coral (% cover/COTS/year). Corresponds to alpha_slow ≈ 0.2, representing lower preference for slow-growing corals.
Log of fast coral intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_fast ≈ 0.8, representing rapid growth of Acropora species.
Log of slow coral intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_slow ≈ 0.2, representing slower growth of Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of fast coral carrying capacity (% cover). Corresponds to K_fast ≈ 50%, representing maximum potential cover of fast-growing corals.
Log of slow coral carrying capacity (% cover). Corresponds to K_slow ≈ 40%, representing maximum potential cover of slow-growing corals.
Logit of competition coefficient of slow on fast coral (dimensionless). Corresponds to beta_fast ≈ 0.4, representing moderate competitive effect.
Logit of competition coefficient of fast on slow coral (dimensionless). Corresponds to beta_slow ≈ 0.33, representing moderate competitive effect.
Log of COTS mortality due to coral depletion (year⁻¹). Corresponds to gamma ≈ 0.5, representing increased mortality when coral food is scarce.
Log of temperature effect on COTS growth (°C⁻¹). Corresponds to delta ≈ 2.0, representing width of temperature tolerance curve.
Log of optimal temperature for COTS (°C). Corresponds to temp_opt ≈ 28°C, representing ideal temperature for COTS reproduction and growth.
Log of survival rate of immigrant COTS larvae (dimensionless). Corresponds to imm_survival ≈ 0.5, representing proportion of immigrant larvae that survive to adulthood.
Log of observation error SD for COTS. Corresponds to sigma_cots ≈ 0.3, representing measurement uncertainty in COTS surveys.
Log of observation error SD for fast coral. Corresponds to sigma_fast ≈ 0.4, representing measurement uncertainty in fast coral cover estimates.
Log of observation error SD for slow coral. Corresponds to sigma_slow ≈ 0.4, representing measurement uncertainty in slow coral cover estimates.
Vector of years for time series
